ISA.name: Authorization Information Qualifier
ISA.description: Code identifying the type of information in the Authorization Information

ISA.name: Authorization Information
ISA.description: Information used for additional identification or authorization of the interchange sender or the data in the interchange; the type of information is set by the Authorization Information Qualifier (I01)

ISA.name: Security Information Qualifier
ISA.description: Code identifying the type of information in the Security Information

ISA.name: Security Information
ISA.description: This is used for identifying the security information about the interchange sender or the data in the interchange; the type of information is set by the Security Information Qualifier (I03)

ISA.name: Interchange ID Qualifier
ISA.description: Code indicating the system/method of code structure used to designate the sender or receiver ID element being qualified

ISA.name: Interchange Sender ID
ISA.description: Identification code published by the sender for other parties to use as the receiver ID to route data to them; the sender always codes this value in the sender ID element

ISA.name: Interchange Receiver ID
ISA.description: Identification code published by the receiver of the data; When sending, it is used by the sender as their sending ID, thus other parties sending to them will use this as a receiving ID to route data to them

GS.name: Functional Identifier Code
GS.description: Code identifying a group of application related transaction sets

GS.name: Application Sender's Code
GS.description: Code identifying party sending transmission; codes agreed to by trading partners

ST.name: Transaction Set Identifier Code
ST.description: Code uniquely identifying a Transaction Set

ST.name: Identifying control number that must be unique within the transaction set functional group assigned by the originator for a transaction set

AK1.name: Functional Identifier Code
AK1.description: Code identifying a group of application related transaction sets

AK1.name: Group Control Number
AK1.description: Assigned number originated and maintained by the sender
